Patch Set 13: Code-Review+1
May be we can have waitedSetupRead method or something equivalent that can be called in place of setup and handleResponse can continue to use restartRead with normal pollTime.

Will this not cause time gap between two polls for fan to become startUpDelay time. We may want to keep start up delay of 5 seconds for fans to come up to right speed and then start polling for their values once every second. Current patch will make both 5 seconds.

This change would only set the wait time of the first poll to what you configured in entity-manager yaml. The subsequent wait time would be set in handleResponse to "pwmPollMs" which is 500ms by default, and the flow for polling would go in circle between waitAndRead -> setupRead - > handleReseponse -> waitAndRead. 

I have tested this patch on my unit and observed only the initial poll of each fan sensor has been set to the configured wait time, and the subsequent poll intervals are 500ms.

I see the poll time might be set to "sensorFailedPollTimeMs(5000ms)" if poll fail occurs, is that the case?

Thanks for explanation. Now understood this comment is not a problem.

> I see the poll time might be set to "sensorFailedPollTimeMs(5000ms)" if poll fail occurs, is that the case?

I didn't mean for this.
waitTimeMs to make the unit clear
Done
Done
startupDelayMs so the unit is clear
Done
Done
some range checking here?
For now it's using uint and the default delay would be 0ms. Are you talking about the maximum delay time?
I realize it can be hard to define a good maximum. But at the same time not having any upper bound is problematic. Yes, I recommend to have a maximum defined.

Yes, it would be hard to find an appropriate maximum because it's hardware dependent. Some fan controllers might just need 1~2s, some need 10s like https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/68874/3?tab=comments. I can set the maximum to 30s or 60s that probably would be sufficient to most platforms or you have any suggestion?
I would be ok with 30 or 60 as the maximum.
I set the maximum to 60s.
Is it OK if you update the `PowerState` property in the Entity-Manager configure to `ChassisOn` or `On` to delay FAN reading. In this case, you don't have to add `StartUpDelay` property.
It seems that your change did not effect if the `PowerState` is "ChassisOn"/"On"? Do you have plan to support this case?

Yes, the change only has effect in "always" state since the controller might need time to retrieve fan speed after enabled. In other state the controller has enough time to initialize the value so we don't have plan to do that.
nit: startupDelay is in ms? better to mention the unit as Zhikui also pointed
Done
nit: pollTimeMs

This pollTime variable is already exist and used in many places. All I do is changing the function name from restartRead to waitAndRead. I can see the unit for this variable is ms. Do you want me to change it to pollTimeMs?
use constexpr
